In [9]:
# Transform string to dictionary
def extract(line):
    pattern_key = "\'([a-z_]+)\'\:"
    pattern_value = "(0.[0-9]+)"
    key_list = re.findall(pattern_key, line)
    value_list = re.findall(pattern_value, line)
    dictionary = {k:float(v) for k,v in zip(key_list, value_list)}
    return dictionary
In [10]:

# Find the top topics
sum_dict_LDA_url = {}

for dictionary in df_LDA_by_page_url['weighted_topics']:
    for key, value in dictionary.items():
        if key not in sum_dict_LDA_url:
            sum_dict_LDA_url[key] = 1
        else:
            sum_dict_LDA_url[key] += 1
            
sum_dict_LDA_url = dict(sorted(sum_dict_LDA_url.items(), key=lambda item: item[1], reverse = True))
In [12]:
keys = [key for key in list(sum_dict_LDA_url.keys())[:50] if key not in unuseful_keys][:10]
values = [sum_dict_LDA_url[key] for key in list(sum_dict_LDA_url.keys())[:50] if key not in unuseful_keys][:10]

plt.figure(figsize=(16, 14))
# Create a bar chart
bar = plt.bar(keys, values, color = '#9FBCF9')
plt.bar_label(bar, values)

# Add labels and title
plt.xlabel('Topic')
plt.ylabel('Number of occurence')
plt.title('Top 10 topics by URL using LDA')

# Show the chart
plt.show()

2.1.5 By TextRazor¶

In [25]:
sum_dict_text_razor = {}
average_scores_list = []

for dictionary in text_razor_df['weighted_topics']:
    dictionary = eval(dictionary)
    if len(dictionary.keys()) > 0:
        for key, value in dictionary.items():
            average_scores_list.extend(list(dictionary.values()))
            if key not in sum_dict_text_razor:
                sum_dict_text_razor[key] = 1
            else:
                sum_dict_text_razor[key] += 1

sum_dict_text_razor = dict(sorted(sum_dict_text_razor.items(), key=lambda item: item[1], reverse = True))

print(np.mean(average_scores_list))

keys = list(sum_dict_text_razor.keys())[:10]
values = list(sum_dict_text_razor.values())[:10]

# Find the top topics for gender
possible_values  = ['male', 'female']
for possible_value in possible_values:
    sum_dict_LDA_url_by_age = {}

    df_LDA_by_page_url_by_age = df_LDA_by_page_url[df_LDA_by_page_url['gender_char']==possible_value]

    for dictionary in df_LDA_by_page_url_by_age['weighted_topics']:
        for key, value in dictionary.items():
            if key not in sum_dict_LDA_url_by_age:
                sum_dict_LDA_url_by_age[key] = 1
            else:
                sum_dict_LDA_url_by_age[key] += 1

    sum_dict_LDA_url_by_age = dict(sorted(sum_dict_LDA_url_by_age.items(), key=lambda item: item[1], reverse = True))

    keys = [key for key in list(sum_dict_LDA_url_by_age.keys())[:50] if key not in unuseful_keys][:10]
    values = [sum_dict_LDA_url_by_age[key] for key in list(sum_dict_LDA_url_by_age.keys())[:50] if key not in unuseful_keys][:10]

    plt.figure(figsize=(16, 14))
    # Create a bar chart
    bar = plt.bar(keys, values, color = '#9FBCF9')
    plt.bar_label(bar, values)

    # Add labels and title
    plt.xlabel('Topic')
    plt.ylabel('Number of occurence')
    plt.title('Top 10 topics by URL using LDA - ' + possible_value)

    # Show the chart
    plt.show()
